# LangGraph Pipeline Graph Module

Implement the complete `pipeline/graph/` module — the LangGraph orchestration layer that ties every prior module together. This is the heart of the pipeline: a compiled `StateGraph` where each processing stage is a node, the `PipelineState` TypedDict threads data through them, and conditional edges route execution depending on confidence thresholds, domain suitability, and errors.

---

## Proposed Changes

### `graph/` — new top-level package

#### [NEW] `graph/__init__.py`
Exports `research_pipeline` (the compiled graph) and `PipelineState`.

---

### `graph/state.py`
Defines `PipelineState` as a `TypedDict`. Fields map 1-to-1 to the spec:

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `run_id` | `str` | UUID string of the pipeline run |
| `paper_id` | `str \| None` | UUID string, set after ingest |
| `pdf_storage_path` | `str \| None` | Supabase Storage path |
| `pdf_bytes` | `bytes \| None` | In-memory PDF, fetched once and reused |
| `paper_metadata` | `PaperMetadata \| None` | Bibliographic info |
| `domain` | `str \| None` | e.g. `"Computer Vision"` |
| `sub_domain` | `str \| None` | e.g. `"Object Detection"` |
| `classification_confidence` | `float` | 0–1 |
| `extraction` | `AiMlExtraction \| None` | Full structured extraction |
| `summaries` | `list[SummaryOutput]` | One per level |
| `diagrams` | `list[DiagramOutput]` | One per diagram type |
| `code_output` | `CodeOutput \| None` | Generated code artefacts |
| `report_path` | `str \| None` | Supabase Storage path to the report |
| `stage_statuses` | `dict[str, StageStatus]` | Per-stage status enum |
| `errors` | `list[str]` | Accumulated error messages |
| `token_usage` | `dict[str, int]` | Tokens per stage |
| `cached_stages` | `set[str]` | Stages served from cache |

All fields carry `NotRequired` defaults so the state can be partially initialised via `make_initial_state()`.

---

### `graph/nodes/` — one file per stage

Every node follows the same contract:
```python
def <name>_node(state: PipelineState) -> dict[str, Any]:
```
Nodes return a **partial state dict** (LangGraph merges it). They never mutate `state` in place.

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/ingest.py`
- Accepts PDF bytes (`state["pdf_bytes"]`), arXiv URL, or DOI (from `state["paper_metadata"]`)
- For arXiv: fetches PDF using `arxiv` package
- For DOI: resolves via CrossRef `https://doi.org/` redirect using `httpx`
- Computes SHA-256 content hash; checks DB for duplicates → raises `DuplicatePaperError`
- Uploads raw PDF to Supabase Storage `papers` bucket via `supabase-py`
- Creates `PaperORM` row in Postgres (via SQLAlchemy async session)
- Updates state: `pdf_storage_path`, `paper_id`
- Emits `STAGE_COMPLETED` on `default_bus`
- On error: appends to `state["errors"]`, sets `stage_statuses["ingest"] = FAILED`

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/classify.py`
- Cache check: query `extractions` table for existing classification for this paper + schema version
- Fetches PDF bytes from Supabase Storage if not already in state
- Renders `prompts/classify_v1.j2` Jinja2 template
- Calls LiteLLM with Gemini vision model; parses JSON response into a `ClassificationResult` Pydantic model (domain, sub_domain, confidence)
- Writes result to state; emits event

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/extract.py`
- Cache check: if extraction exists in DB for same paper + schema version, load and mark cached
- Renders `prompts/extract_v1.j2` with domain & sub_domain context
- Sends PDF bytes + rendered prompt to Gemini via LiteLLM + Instructor
- Instructor validates response against `AiMlExtraction` schema; auto-retries on failure
- Stores validated extraction in `extractions` DB table as JSONB
- Tracks tokens via `TelemetryCollector`; updates `token_usage`

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/summarise.py`
- Works entirely from `state["extraction"]` (no PDF needed)
- Renders `prompts/summarise_v1.j2` with extraction JSON
- Makes 4 separate LiteLLM calls (one per `SummaryLevel`)
- Stores `SummaryOutput` records into `outputs` table
- Updates `state["summaries"]`

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/embed.py`
- Works from `state["extraction"]`
- Prepares 4 embedding chunks: title+abstract, key contributions, proposed method, results
- Calls `litellm.embedding()` with `gemini/text-embedding-004` for each chunk
- Stores 768-d vectors in `embeddings` table via pgvector (`EmbeddingORM`)
- Updates state with confirmation key

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/diagram.py`
- Works from `state["extraction"]`
- Renders `prompts/diagram_v1.j2` with architecture + flow descriptions
- Makes 3 LiteLLM calls (ARCHITECTURE, TRAINING_FLOW, INFERENCE_FLOW)
- Validates Mermaid syntax via subprocess (`mmdc --input` or regex guard)
- On invalid syntax: retries with error feedback (up to `max_retries`)
- Uploads SVG files to Supabase Storage `outputs` bucket
- Stores `DiagramOutput` records; updates `state["diagrams"]`

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/codegen.py`
- Works from `state["extraction"]`
- Renders `prompts/codegen_v1.j2` with architecture, training procedure, dataset descriptions
- Sends to Gemini via LiteLLM; returns PyTorch implementation skeleton
- Validates with `ast.parse()` — retries with syntax error feedback on failure
- Exports `.py` file and Jupyter notebook via `nbformat`
- Uploads both to Supabase Storage; stores `CodeOutput`; updates state

#### [NEW] `graph/nodes/report.py`
- Works from full state (summaries, diagrams, code, extraction, paper_metadata)
- Assembles structured Markdown report (paper metadata, paragraph summary, key contributions, embedded SVG diagrams, section-by-section summary, implementation notes, code snippet, extraction JSON)
- Uploads Markdown to Supabase Storage
- Stores `ReportOutput`; updates `state["report_path"]`
- Emits `RUN_COMPLETED` on `default_bus`

