## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Parallelism**: The spec says "parallel edges from extract to summarise, embed, diagram, codegen." Pure LangGraph `StateGraph` can model this with `Send()` or by simply chaining the nodes sequentially (summarise → embed → diagram → codegen → report). Since the pipeline is not async-concurrent today and state merging with fan-in requires extra plumbing, I propose the sequential layout. Should I implement true concurrent fan-out using LangGraph's `Send()` API, or is sequential fine?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Supabase / DB calls in nodes**: The nodes as designed will need a live Supabase client and an async SQLAlchemy session. For now, nodes will import `db.session.get_async_session` and `supabase-py`. Should I add `supabase` (Python client) to `pyproject.toml` dependencies, or is that already managed elsewhere?

> [!NOTE]
> **Prompts directory**: Jinja2 prompt templates are referenced but not yet in the repo. I'll create stubs in `pipeline/prompts/` with placeholder content so the graph can be imported and tested structurally without a live LLM.

